    Scope and Contents
The narrators discuss personnel, machines, operations and types of bricks manufactured at the Poston Brick Company in Springfield. Narrators also discuss working conditions, hazards, co-workers, and the structures located on the factory grounds.5 tapes, 240 mins., 78 pp.
Interviews by Garnetta Cook, 1972
